---
name: react-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for React component development and state management
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
---

- Use functional components with hooks
- Keep components small and focused
- Utilize memoization for performance optimization
- Implement proper prop type validation

---
name: typescript-best-practices.mdc
description: TypeScript coding standards and type safety guidelines
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx}
---

- Use strict null checks
- Prefer interface over type when possible
- Use type guards and assertions for runtime type checking
- Implement proper type inference to reduce explicit type annotations

---
name: emotion-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for using Emotion for styling in React
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
---

- Use `styled` for component-specific styles
- Utilize the `css` prop for dynamic styling
- Implement a consistent naming convention for styled components
- Use Emotion's theming capabilities for global style management

---
name: material-ui-best-practices.mdc
description: Guidelines for using Material-UI components and theming
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
---

- Use Material-UI's theme provider for consistent styling
- Customize components using the `sx` prop for fine-grained control
- Implement responsive design using Material-UI's breakpoints
- Utilize Material-UI's icon library for consistent iconography

---
name: react-query-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for data fetching and caching with React Query
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
---

- Use `useQuery` for fetching data and `useMutation` for updates
- Implement proper query keys for efficient caching and refetching
- Utilize `queryClient` for manual cache management when needed
- Set appropriate stale time and cache time for performance optimization

---
name: axios-best-practices.mdc
description: Guidelines for using Axios for HTTP requests
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
---

- Use interceptors for global request/response handling
- Implement proper error handling and status code checking
- Utilize Axios' cancel token for aborting requests when necessary
- Set appropriate timeouts for requests to prevent hanging

---
name: vite-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for using Vite as a development and build tool
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
---

- Use Vite's plugin system for extending functionality
- Implement proper environment variable management
- Utilize Vite's hot module replacement for development efficiency
- Optimize build configuration for production performance